Question: Should the government provide free college education to everyone the same way it provides high school education? Explain your answer.
Answer:
It will be awesome that government provides free college education to everyone. But it is unrealistic and unnecessary to do that. First of all, college education is far more expensive than high school education. The government may not be capable to cover the cost or afford it to the entire public for free. Second, college education is not necessary for everyone. People have different career plans after high school. College education is not an option for everyone.